
Overview of adj fiery

The adj fiery has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (2) ardent, fervent, fervid, fiery, impassioned, perfervid, torrid -- (characterized by intense emotion; "ardent love"; "an ardent lover"; "a fervent desire to change society"; "a fervent admirer"; "fiery oratory"; "an impassioned appeal"; "a torrid love affair")
2. (2) fiery, igneous -- (like or suggestive of fire; "a fiery desert wind"; "an igneous desert atmosphere")
3. fiery, flaming -- (very intense; "a fiery temper"; "flaming passions")
